AB  - Building Performance Simulation (BPS) is critical in architecture and engineering education but remains challenging to teach, particularly to students with limited technical backgrounds. This study introduces a novel solution: a crowdsourced campus digital twin platform with tailored BPS pedagogy. Our platform hosts student-developed models and simulation templates, offering a hands-on, interactive learning environment. Over 50 first-year undergraduate students submitted 22 models. The crowdsourced element encouraged peer assessment, allowing students to compare and critically evaluate their work. Course evaluation feedback scores for this course - across various categories - surpassed departmental and faculty averages, validating the method's effectiveness. Students highlighted the engaging and practical nature of the approach, although some found the learning curve steep and requested more foundational guidance. Overall, the findings demonstrate the value of this collaborative platform in fostering BPS learning, while also serving as a repository of multiscale data for future research.
